Third-party software
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GIAS is built on open-source components, each distributed under its own license.
Key dependencies include Streamlit, Haystack (deepset), Pydantic, pandas, Plotly,
WeasyPrint, PyMuPDF, and pypdf. See requirements.txt for the full list and the
respective projects for their license terms.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Data sources
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GIAS aggregates data from external biodiversity databases at query time. The
data returned belongs to those providers and is subject to their terms of use:
GBIF, WRiMS, IUCN Red List, EASIN, AquaNIS, and CABI.
